==English==
'''degree Celsius'''

===Eytmology===

:Named after the Swedish astronomer Anders Celsius.

===Noun===

#A [[metric]] [[unit]] of [[temperature]], a [[derived unit]] of the [[International System of Units]].  Symbol: °C (''Note: in technical contexts, the symbol should always included the degree symbol ° to prevent possible confusion with C, the symbol for coulombs.  In informal usage, where the meaning is clear, the degree symbol is sometimes omitted.'')  Compare [[kelvin]], [[degree Fahrenheit]].

